On 05/12/2017 09:24 AM, wolfree@... [archive-crawler] wrote:
&gt; Hi there,
&gt;   
&gt;
&gt;   We are now using finally Heritrix with Umbra and got it finally working with Heritrix 3.3.
&gt;   We now are looking for a possibility to only crawl the first site(s) with Umbra. Is there a bean or something?
&gt;   
&gt;
&gt;   Cheers

I just saw this. Do you mean you only want to send the seed url to 
Umbra? Then add the following to the AMQPPublishProcessor bean:

&lt;property name=&quot;shouldProcessRule&quot;&gt;
    &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.DecideRuleSequence&quot;&gt;
     &lt;property name=&quot;rules&quot;&gt;
      &lt;list&gt;
       &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.RejectDecideRule&quot; /&gt;
       &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.HopsPathMatchesRegexDecideRule&quot;&gt;
        &lt;property name=&quot;regex&quot; value=&quot;^$&quot;/&gt;
       &lt;/bean&gt;
      &lt;/list&gt;
     &lt;/property&gt;
    &lt;/bean&gt;
   &lt;/property&gt;

The regex means that you only process links for which the discovery path 
is empty - ie. seeds.

We use &quot;^$|.*L&quot; so we process all actual webpages.

